# Architecture rules

The authoritative rules live in `AGENTS.md` at the repo root. Follow it. Summary:

- Hexagonal (ports & adapters). Imports point **inward only**:
  `infrastructure/ → application/ → domain/`.
- `src/app/domain/` is pure: no FastAPI, SQLAlchemy, loguru, pydantic-settings, or any
  `application`/`infrastructure` import. Business-rule violations raise domain exceptions.
- `src/app/application/` orchestrates domain objects through ports. `ports/input/` = driving
  contracts; `ports/output/` = driven contracts implemented in `infrastructure/`. No infra
  libraries here.
- `src/app/infrastructure/` holds every concrete technology and implements the output ports.
- The boundary is enforced by import-linter (`uv run poe arch`). Do not break it to make
  code compile — invert the dependency with an output port instead.

# Definition of done

A change is complete only when `uv run poe check` is green (ruff → ty → import-linter →
deptry → pip-audit → pytest+coverage+schemathesis). Mirror the `Task` slice for new
features; see `docs/adding-a-feature.md`. Conventional Commits; Google-style docstrings;
line length 120; type hints on everything.
